 may correspond to the\nobserved asymmetries. Moreover, the present disk shape suggests that the planet\nis on an eccentric orbit. The scenario we explored is a natural hypothesis if\nthe planet formed within a disk. Conversely, its low probability of occurrence\nand the fact that HD 106906 b shares some characteristics with other systems in\nSco-Cen (e.g. HIP 78530, in terms of mass ratio and separation) may indicate an\nalternative formation pathway for those objects.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Mar 2017 13:17:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Mar 2017 10:56:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-24"}
